"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753537","Home Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>Due to the way in which absconder data is recorded, it is not currently feasible to make an informed estimate of the number of people who have absconded from ports of entry after being stopped by Border Force, or who were subsequently recovered.</p><p> </p><p>To establish this information would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-24T13:25:30.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753537/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753537/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-18","Immigration Controls: Undocumented Migrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people absconded from ports of entry after being stopped by Border Force officers in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","5750"
