"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752516","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-24","<p>Since the Grenfell Tower fire the Department has worked in partnership with multiple agencies. Officials have continued to support local resilience forums and have participated in meetings with key emergency planning stakeholders.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-24T15:57:51.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752516/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752516/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-17","Buildings: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what advice he has sought from Local Resilience Forums on ensuring building safety following the Grenfell Tower fire.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","5242"
